domain.description: The Fast Healthcare Interoperability Resources (FHIR) standard is a set of rules and specifications for exchanging electronic health care data. It is designed to be flexible and adaptable, so that it can be used in a wide range of settings and with different health care information systems. Its goal is to enable the seamless and secure exchange of health care information, so that patients can receive the best possible care.

specification.description: REST service API used by FHIR servers and clients for the exchange of patient data.

actor.name: FHIR server

testSuite.description: Test suite defining test scenarios for FHIR clients and servers to verify their correct usage of the FHIR service API specifications.

testCase.description: The FHIR client submits a specific allergy intollerance to a FHIR server with evidence of its correct processing.
testCase.documentation:
FHIR client test case 1: Submit allergy intolerances

The FHIR client submits a specific allergy intollerance to a FHIR server with evidence of its correct processing. The detailed steps for this test case are presented in the following sequence diagram:

Test case notes:

  • For more information on the FHIR web service API specifications please refer to the FHIR documentation.
  • You can choose in your configuration whether the test data should be deleted as a first test step.
  • Messages sent between client and server are expected to be for patient "example".

parameter.name: embeddedFhirServerEndpoint
parameter.description: The endpoint of the internal FHIR server used to validate client requests.

parameter.name: ingestDataPerTestSession
parameter.description: Whether or not the internal FHIR server needs to ingest the test dataset before each test session.

parameter.name: manualCheckTimeout
parameter.description: The maximum time (in milliseconds) to wait for an administrator to manually check a test session (30 minutes).

parameter.name: messagingServiceAddress
parameter.description: The address for the GITB messaging service's WSDL definition.

parameter.name: processingServiceAddress
parameter.description: The address for the GITB processing service's WSDL definition.

parameter.name: validationServiceAddress
parameter.description: The address for the GITB validation service's WSDL definition.

parameter.name: validatorFailureSeverity
parameter.description: Whether or not validation calls to the FHIR validator will be treated as errors ("ERROR") or warnings ("WARNING").

property.name: verboseHelp
property.label: Show verbose help in tests
property.description: Whether or not you will see popups during test sessions with instructions on next steps (besides log messages that are always added).

property.name: ingestDataPerTestSession
property.label: Set up dataset per test session
property.description: Whether or not to setup the test dataset before each test session executes.

property.name: serverApiRoot
property.label: FHIR server API root
property.description: The API root for the FHIR server (provided without a trailing slash).

landingPage.name: Default
landingPage.content:
Welcome to the FHIR® Test Bed

This is a conformance testing service to facilitate testing against the FHIR® specifications.

Currently the FHIR® web service API specification is supported, with test cases for servers and clients. To begin testing:

  1. Register one or more systems to test for conformance.
  2. Create client or server conformance statements based on your systems' testing goal.
  3. Execute the configured statements' tests.

In case of assistance you may contact the service desk at fhir-support@imec.be.
